{"questionId":"32941288","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The amount of material used for each container can be modelled by the external surface area of the container.</p>\n<p>The external surface area, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi></math>, of the container can be expressed as</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mi>k</mi><mi>r</mi></mfrac></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; (Substitution of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>400</mn><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac></math> in <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mi>r</mi><mi>h</mi></math>)</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mi>r</mi><mi>h</mi></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to isolate <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(M1)<br></strong></em><br><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>400</mn><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac></math><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<p>correct substitution of their <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi></math> into correct expression<em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(M1)<br></strong></em><br><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mi>r</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mn>400</mn><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>A</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>800</mn><mi>r</mi></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math><br><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>800</mn></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; (</strong>Equating <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mi>r</mi><mi>h</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>k</mi><mi>r</mi></mfrac></math>)<strong><br></strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mi>r</mi><mi>h</mi></math> &nbsp; <strong>OR&nbsp;&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mi>r</mi><mi>h</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>k</mi><mi>r</mi></mfrac></math><em> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; (A1)</em></strong></p>\n<p>attempt to isolate <em>h</em><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(M1)<br></strong></em><br><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>400</mn><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>correct substitution of their <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi></math> into <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mi>r</mi><mi>h</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mi>k</mi><mi>r</mi></mfrac></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(M1)<br></strong></em><br><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mi>r</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mn>400</mn><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>k</mi><mi>r</mi></mfrac></math><strong>&nbsp;<br><br><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>800</mn></math><em> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A1</em></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><strong><em>[4 marks]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"32941288","referenceCode":"24N.2.SL.TZ1.4d","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the value of k.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"d","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.3—Differentiating polynomials, n E Z"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}